<ServicePage
  title="Custom AI Agent Development"
  description="Purpose-built AI agents that handle your repetitive, structured workflows — sales outreach, data entry, report generation, customer triage — so your team can focus on the work that actually requires a human."
>
  <section>
    <h2>What We Build</h2>
    <p>
      We build AI agents that do real work inside your business. Not chatbots. Not copilots. Agents with jobs — specific workflows they execute on a schedule or on demand, using your existing tools.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Task-specific agents</strong> — Each agent is built for one job and does it well: prospecting, data extraction, report prep, follow-up sequences, inbox triage</li>
      <li><strong>Tool integration</strong> — Agents connect to what you already use: Google Workspace, CRMs, spreadsheets, databases, email, Slack</li>
      <li><strong>Human oversight built in</strong> — Agents draft, stage, and flag. Humans review, approve, and send. You stay in control</li>
      <li><strong>Persistent memory</strong> — Agents remember context across runs, so they get smarter about your business over time</li>
      <li><strong>Transparent operation</strong> — Full logging, audit trails, and clear boundaries on what the agent can and can't do</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Every agent we build is custom. Your workflows, your tools, your rules. No SaaS platform to outgrow, no per-seat pricing, no generic templates.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>We follow a structured process to get from "I wish someone would handle this" to a working agent:</p>

    <h3>Stage 1: Workflow Mapping</h3>
    <p>
      We sit down with you and map the workflow end-to-end. What triggers it? What tools are involved? What decisions get made along the way? Where does a human need to stay in the loop? This is where we figure out what's actually automatable vs. what needs judgment.
    </p>

    <h3>Stage 2: Agent Design</h3>
    <p>
      We design the agent's architecture: what model powers it, what tools it needs access to, what data it reads and writes, what guardrails keep it in bounds. You review and approve the design before we write a line of code.
    </p>

    <h3>Stage 3: Build & Test</h3>
    <p>
      We build the agent against your real data and tools — not a sandbox. You see working output within the first sprint. We iterate based on what the agent actually produces, not mockups or slide decks.
    </p>

    <h3>Stage 4: Deploy & Monitor</h3>
    <p>
      The agent goes live on your infrastructure. We set up scheduling, monitoring, and alerting. You get documentation and training so your team knows exactly what's running and how to manage it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Our Approach</h2>

    <div class="service-tier">
      <h4>Discovery Sprint</h4>
      <p>One week to determine if an AI agent is the right solution for your workflow.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Workflow mapping and analysis</li>
        <li>Tool and integration inventory</li>
        <li>Feasibility assessment and risk identification</li>
        <li>Agent architecture recommendation</li>
        <li>Scope, timeline, and cost estimate for the build</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="service-tier">
      <h4>Agent Build</h4>
      <p>We build, test, and deploy your custom agent against real data and tools.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Custom agent development for your specific workflow</li>
        <li>Integration with your existing tools and data sources</li>
        <li>Human-in-the-loop review workflows</li>
        <li>Memory and context management</li>
        <li>Scheduling, logging, and monitoring setup</li>
        <li>Documentation and team training</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="service-tier">
      <h4>Ongoing Support</h4>
      <p>Continuous refinement as your needs evolve and as AI capabilities improve.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Performance monitoring and tuning</li>
        <li>Workflow adjustments as your process changes</li>
        <li>Additional agent development for new workflows</li>
        <li>Model and tooling upgrades</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Case Study: Drew, AI Sales Agent</h2>
    <div class="case-study">
      <h3>The Problem</h3>
      <p>
        As a solo operator, sales outreach was the first thing to fall off the plate during client engagements. Weeks would pass without a single prospecting email. The pipeline would go cold.
      </p>

      <h3>The Agent</h3>
      <p>
        We built Drew — an AI sales development agent that runs every weekday morning. Drew reads a lead database, prioritizes prospects by signal strength, writes personalized outreach emails using real research about each company, and stages drafts for human review before anything sends.
      </p>

      <h3>The Result</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consistent pipeline</strong> — outreach happens every day, not just when there's time</li>
        <li><strong>Personalized, not templated</strong> — each email references the prospect's specific context</li>
        <li><strong>Full transparency</strong> — Drew's email signature discloses that he's an AI agent</li>
        <li><strong>Human oversight</strong> — every email is reviewed before it sends</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <a href="/blog/meet-drew">Read the full story about Drew →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

